article.description: Carrington Love scored 25 of his career-high 39 points in the second half, and Green Bay topped 100 points for the third time this season in a 107-90 win over Youngstown State on Saturday.
article.headline: Love's 39 helps Green Bay top Youngstown State 107-90
article.linkText: Love's 39 helps Green Bay top Youngstown State 107-90
article.story: ASHWAUBENON, Wis. -- Carrington Love scored 25 of his career-high 39 points in the second half, and Green Bay topped 100 points for the third time this season in a 107-90 win over Youngstown State on Saturday. Green Bay (17-11, 9-6 Horizon) led by as many as 21 points late in the second half, erasing Youngstown State's 18-point first-half advantage. The Penguins (10-18, 5-10) made 9 of 11 3-pointers before the break en route to a 57-45 halftime lead and season high for points in any half this season. Jordan Andrews, who finished with 19 points, was 5 for 5 in the first half from beyond the arc. But Love hit 9 of 15 from the field in the second half, including four 3-pointers, leading the Phoenix to their second straight win after trading wins and losses the past 13 games. Jordan Fouse added 17 points, nine rebounds and six assists for Green Bay.
